description.narrative: (Ghana): People for Health reinforces civil society organizations' leadership and their ability to mobilize community organizations and community members to advocate for better and equitable services, promote accountability in the use of health resources, and maximize the responsiveness of health service providers. With FY 2019 funds, the activity will strengthen the role of civil society by training and equipping local non-governmental organizations in community mobilization, citizenship engagement, and evidence-based advocacy skills for effective tracking of government health resources in the areas of family planning; water, sanitation and hygiene; malaria; nutrition; and HIV.. .
